NOTE ON LICENSE CHANGE
This component was previously licensed under the Apache License 2.0.
It was relicensed to AGPL-3.0 in February 2026 to enable code sharing
with the open-source fediverse ecosystem (Mastodon, Misskey, Pixelfed,
PeerTube, and others) and to ensure community improvements flow back
to the commons. The AGPL does not restrict private use.

---

OPEN SOURCE ATTRIBUTION
This software incorporates patterns, algorithms, and adapted components
from the following open source projects. Full attribution is listed on
the Sojorn licenses page at https://sojorn.net/licenses.

- Matrix / Element (Apache-2.0) — E2EE messaging patterns
- Ushahidi (AGPL-3.0) — Incident map and verification UI patterns
- Discourse (GPL-2.0) — Trust level system design
- Mastodon (AGPL-3.0) — Post visibility and content warning UI
- Misskey (AGPL-3.0) — Reaction system and dashboard layout patterns
- PeerTube (AGPL-3.0) — HLS video player and creator tools patterns
- Pixelfed (AGPL-3.0) — Photo grid and discovery feed patterns
- Hi.Events (AGPL-3.0) — Event creation and RSVP flow patterns
- HumHub (AGPL-3.0) — Community spaces and activity stream patterns

Each of these projects is used in compliance with its respective license.
Adaptations are transformative and constitute original work under AGPL-3.0.
